Sentencas: Laser machining of the nickel oxide-yttria-stabilized zirconia (NiO-YSZ) composite in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) may be an effective approach to enlarge the electrode-electrolyte interface and improve the cell performance.
Titulo: Laser Machining of Nickel Oxide-Yttria Stabilized Zirconia Composite for Surface Modification in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, laser energy can cause thermal damage to the composite surface during the machined operation.
Titulo: Laser Machining of Nickel Oxide-Yttria Stabilized Zirconia Composite for Surface Modification in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this work, the microstructure changes and the collateral damage caused by pulsed laser machining on the sintered NiO-YSZ of the state-of-the-art SOFCs were evaluated using complementary analysis techniques.
Titulo: Laser Machining of Nickel Oxide-Yttria Stabilized Zirconia Composite for Surface Modification in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Laser patterns consisting of parallel tracks on sintered NiO-YSZ were processed, varying the laser parameters such as frequency and laser beam energy density.
Titulo: Laser Machining of Nickel Oxide-Yttria Stabilized Zirconia Composite for Surface Modification in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The analyses evidenced a heat-affected zone (HAZ) limited to around 2 & mu;m with microcracking, porosity reduction, and recrystallization.
Titulo: Laser Machining of Nickel Oxide-Yttria Stabilized Zirconia Composite for Surface Modification in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The changes in chemical composition, phase transformation of YSZ and mechanical properties at the machined surface were quite limited.
Titulo: Laser Machining of Nickel Oxide-Yttria Stabilized Zirconia Composite for Surface Modification in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
